{CIRENCESTER PARK.}
CIRENCESTER PARK IS OPEN TO THE PUBLIC.{THE GEORGIAN LANDSCAPE-GARDEN {STYLE}IS SAID TO BE ONE OF THE FINEST EXAMPLES IN THE COUNTRY AND HAS MANY WALKS AND RIDES. {THE BROAD AVENUE IS {PARTICULARY FINE BEING THE LONGEST {AVENUE IN BRITAIN.}IT RUNS FROM CIRENCESTER TO SAPPERTON, A DISTANCE OF SIX MILES.
THE MIXED WOODLAND IS FAMOUS FOR ITS BEECH TREES AND THE PARK HAS CHANGED BUT LITTLE IN THE LAST TWO HUNDRED YEARS.{THERE ARE TWO GEORGIAN {FOLLIES. "POPE'S SEAT",BUILT FOR THE {POET, ALEXANDER POPE, IS AT THE SEVEN {RIDES AND "ALFRED'S HALL" AT THE TEN {RIDES.
